This game is really close to being 5 stars. It's a lot of fun. Unfortunately, frame rate problems (which existed in essentially the same state a couple of years ago) lead to other issues. When a frame is dropped, things that should have collided in that frame are not recorded as having collided. So an enemy, for example, can skip over your projectile if the right frame I dropped. This is incredibly frustrating, as are the constantly dropping frames on large levels or when the enemy count goes up.

Okay, I have SEVERAL complaints about this app.  1.) FEINT. Freaking FEINT. No, I don't want this service, but A) You can't turn the freaking thing off after saying "NO", it keeps asking, and B)  It launches EVERY SINGLE FREAKING TIME YOU START THE GAME. This should not be a constant intrusion of a PAID GAME we ALREADY PAY MONEY FOR.  2.) Invasive facebook integration. This is seriously a staple of what's wrong in mobile gaming at the moment, and NEEDS AN "OFF, DON'T BUG ME ABOUT IT, LET ME PLAY THE GODDAMN GAME" Button.  3.) This is a ripoff of "Super Crate Box" for the PC, just with some added RPG-esque elements. A FREE GAME.  4.) The controls don't feel very responsive and it's easy to hit one button without intending to (Playing on a Samsung Galaxy S).  All in all, this is a poor game that DOES NOT deserve the amount of money I paid for it. It'd have been excusable if it were only $1, but at this price, the amount of invasiveness due to the above things that are made REALLY hard to ignore (On purpose, I would imagine), this game plays more like a "free" game.  Oh, did I mention it has optional microtransactions to get "more points"?
